### @psi・23  New Innovative DDoS Protection, Improved Text Scoring Robustness and More Emission to the SuperEnsemble


### DDoS Protection
We are introducing a new concept for DDoS protection, where miners will share their axons only with trusted validators, instead of making them available for everyone.

It works by miners having the option to set up a server to serve the axons from, and when validators query it, they get authenticated and get the IP address for the real server, and can query it directly.

Thus, a malicious actor would need to have a access to a major validator in order to learn the axons of a miner. And in doing so, would potentially reveal which validator they are working with, so miners can choose to not share their axon with them.

### Improved Text Scoring Robustness
We are working to enhance the robustness of the scoring of the text models, and thus you may experience increased load on your servers due to higher token requirements.
